merlin_webpac - WebOPAC for the MERLIN Cluster

INSTALLATION

PRE-REQUISITES

 * A Subversion client. A good client for Windows is TortoiseSVN, available at:
   http://tortoisesvn.net/downloads

 * Perl. For Windows, ActivePerl is fine:
   http://www.activestate.com/store/activeperl/download/

 * the following Perl modules

	Template-Toolkit
   	Template-DBI
	Template-Plugin-EnvHash
	Template-XML
	XML-DOM
	XML-RSS
	XML-RegExp
	XML-Twig
	XML-XPath
	libxml-perl

In order to install the above Perl modules on Windows, you'll need to add some
non-Active-state repositories to your Perl Package Manager. Here are the ones
I use:

	Name: bribes.org
	URL: http://www.bribes.org/perl/ppm/package.lst

	Name: University of Winnipeg
	URL: http://theory.uwinnipeg.ca/ppms/package.xml

	Name: trouchelle.com
	URL: http://trouchelle.com/ppm/package.xml

	Name: tcool.org
	URL: http://ppm.tcool.org/archives/package.xml


INSTALLATION

After checking out this project into your workspace, you need to run the configuration script
(bin/configure.pl) with the following options set:

  perl configure.pl -i [your initials]
